SIMPLE: seventeenth
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Seventeenth
<hw>Sev"en*teenth`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Seventeen</er>: cf. AS. <ets>seofonte⟦oacute⟧⟦edh⟧a</ets>,
<ets>seofonteoge⟦edh⟧a</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Next in order
after the sixteenth; coming after sixteen others.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In . . . the <qex>seventeenth</qex> day of the month . . . were
all the fountains of the great deep broken up.</q> <rj><qau>Gen. vii.
11.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Constituting or being one of seventeen equal parts
into which anything is divided.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Seventeenth</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Seventeenth
<hw>Sev"en*teenth`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
next in order after the sixteenth; one coming after sixteen
others.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The quotient of a unit divided by seventeen; one of
seventeen equal parts or divisions of one whole.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>An interval of two octaves and a
third.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Seventh</ent>⟦br⟧
